Results
aseline characteristics are shown in able. Β 1. Thirty-one patients were studied with a mean age of 38β€‰Β±β€‰13 years (range 16 to 65Β years) and of whom 20 were male (65%). These patients carried five different mutated genes, one patient carried a double-heterozygous mutation. Mean LVED mass and LVEF were 76β€‰Β±β€‰23 g/m2 and 67β€‰Β±β€‰5% respectively. LVEDWT(max) was 20β€‰Β±β€‰7 mm (range 9 to 32Β mm). Twenty-three (74%) patients had an LVEDWT(max) of β‰¥15Β mm. Fibrosis was present in 21 (68%) patients. In these patients, the extent of fibrosis was 4.9β€‰Β±β€‰4.3% of LV mass. ERVA (VPBs but not VT or VF) occurred in 7 (23%) patients. One patient had a bigeminy and couplet during the recovery phase.
