All patients with ERVA had myocardial fibrosis on CMR, whereas fibrosis was only observed in 58% of the patients without ERVA (100% vs. 58%, pβ€‰=β€‰0.04). In patients with ERVA, the extent of fibrosis was significantly larger than in patients without ERVA (8β€‰Β±β€‰4% vs. 3β€‰Β±β€‰3%, pβ€‰=β€‰0.02).
The LVEDWT(max) and NT-proBNP levels did not significantly differ between patients with and without ERVA (23β€‰Β±β€‰7 mm vs. 19β€‰Β±β€‰7 mm, pβ€‰=β€‰0.2 and 87β€‰Β±β€‰53 pmol/l vs. 62β€‰Β±β€‰57 pmol/l, pβ€‰=β€‰0.3, respectively).
No significant differences in concomitant Ξ²-blocker therapy, gender, age or mutated gene were found between patients with and without ERVA. All patients with ERVA had one or more risk factors for SCD (100% vs. 58%, pβ€‰=β€‰0.04) (TableΒ 2) [15]. There was no significant difference in the presence of fibrosis between the carriers of the different gene mutations (pβ€‰=β€‰0.7).
